verses.roman:
jāniyāo svarūpa gosāñi prabhure puchila
'ei tarajāra artha bujhite nārila'

synonyms: jāniyāo—although knowing; svarūpa gosāñi—Svarūpa Dāmodara Gosvāmī; prabhure puchila—inquired from Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; ei tarajāra artha—the meaning of this sonnet; bujhite—to understand; nārila—I was not able.
translation: Although he knew the secret, Svarūpa Dāmodara Gosvāmī inquired from the Lord, "What is the meaning of this sonnet? I could not understand it."
